comment: Cousins (SAC) dislodges George (IND), affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Turner (IND) jumps from point A to point B and makes contact with Cousins (SAC) after he begins his shooting motion.
George (IND) makes incidental contact with Temple (SAC) that does not dislodge him from his legal guarding position.
Cousins (SAC) makes contact with George (IND) inside of the restricted area on the driving shot attempt. The foul call is incorrectly attributed to Temple (SAC).
Temple (SAC) allows George (IND) to land following the jump shot attempt.
Allen (IND) maintains legal guarding position on the drive to the basket by Cousins (SAC) and makes contact with the ball.
Cousins (SAC) makes incidental contact with Teague (IND) that does not affect his SQBR.
[Observable in enhanced video] Turner (IND) moves his pivot foot.
Afflalo (SAC) legally contests George's (IND) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the game clock is reset to 00:00.6.
Robinson III (IND) maintains legal guarding position during Cousins' (SAC) shot attempt.
George (IND) legally contests Afflalo's (SAC) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Cousins (SAC) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Temple (SAC) makes incidental contact with George (IND) that does not affect his SQBR.
Temple (SAC) makes incidental contact with George (IND) during rebounding.
Robinson III (IND) makes marginal contact with Cousins (SAC) that does not affect his FOM.
IND does not return to the playing court in a timely manner following the timeout.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of SAC possession is overturned and IND is awarded possession.
George (IND) maintains legal guarding position and blocks the shot attempt by Cousins (SAC). Any contact is incidental.
George (IND) cleanly strips the ball from Cousins (SAC) and it goes out of bounds.
[Observable in enhanced video] Collison (SAC) moves his pivot foot.
Young (IND) makes incidental contact with Collison (SAC) that does not affect his SQBR.
Miles (IND) legally contests Temple's (SAC) jump shot attempt.
Cousins (SAC) and Allen (IND) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
George (IND) and Cousins (SAC) make incidental contact with one another during the loose ball.
Teague (IND) maintains legal guarding position on the drive to the basket and shot attempt by Collison (SAC) and the contact is incidental.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of IND possession stands.
Cousins (SAC) commits a take foul on George (IND).
Tolliver (SAC) commits a take foul on Teague (IND).
